{"id":529,"date":"2014-03-26T11:11:57","date_gmt":"2014-03-26T11:11:57","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/rstp.fantomdesign.net\/?page_id=529"},"modified":"2023-03-14T11:56:55","modified_gmt":"2023-03-14T15:56:55","slug":"country-condition-information","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.rstp.ca\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/","title":{"rendered":"Country Condition Information"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><strong><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-414 alignleft\" style=\"margin: 0 20px 20px 0;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.rstp.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/03\/country-conditions-lighter-blue-300x157.jpg\" alt=\"country-conditions-lighter-blue\" width=\"300\" height=\"157\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.rstp.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/03\/country-conditions-lighter-blue-300x157.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.rstp.ca\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/03\/country-conditions-lighter-blue.jpg 673w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>Welcome<\/strong> to the Country Condition Information resource page!<\/p>\n<p>The sources and summaries compiled here provide information about the conditions in a refugee&#8217;s country of origin to help refugee sponsors in the assessment of potential cases for sponsorship. Conducting country condition research allows private refugee sponsoring groups to strengthen their understanding of eligibility issues and improve their planning and preparation work. The information is intended to serve as a starting point of such research and is by no means extensive, however care has been taken to draw on legitimate sources and highlight persecution trends. The following countries profiled have been selected based on sponsorship and landing trends of privately sponsored refugees over the last five years.<\/p>\n<p><i>Disclaimer: Please note that this compilation and resource is not intended to provide legal advice. For legal advice, definitions and requirements, please consult a legal professional and review government laws, policies and guidelines (e.g.: The Immigration and Refugee Protection Act and Immigration and Refugee Protection Regulations).<\/i><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #993300;\"><strong>For the most updated information, please consult the Country of Origin Information Packages compiled by the Immigration and Refugee Board of Canada, <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><a style=\"color: #0000ff;\" href=\"http:\/\/www.irb-cisr.gc.ca\/Eng\/ResRec\/NdpCnd\/Pages\/ndpcnd.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">available online here<\/a><\/span>. These packages are available for every country and provide detailed information on issues and conditions in the country of origin.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<h2>Please select a country of origin:<\/h2>\n<div class='content-column one_third'><div style=\"padding-right:20px;\"><h3><strong>Africa<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/democratic-republic-of-congo\/\">DR Congo<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/eritrea\/\">Eritrea<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/ethiopia\/\">Ethiopia<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/somalia\/\">Somalia<\/a><\/p><\/div><\/div>\n<div class='content-column one_third'><div style=\"padding-right:20px;\"><h3><strong>Asia \/ Middle-East<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/afghanistan\/\">Afghanistan<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/iran\/\">Iran<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/iraq\/\">Iraq<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/myanmarburma\/\">Myanmar\/Burma<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/sri-lanka\/\">Sri Lanka<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"\/en\/refugees\/country-condition-information\/syria\/\">Syria<\/a><\/p><\/div><\/div><div class='content-colum